m provides the JVM-facing API contracts used to build MockK agents, including proxy makers, invocation handlers, cancellation handles, and class-transformation requests. It is consumed by MockK agent implementations to create regular, constructor, static, and inline mocks for Kotlin and Java tests on the JVM.\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-api-jvm/index.json:18:      \"io.mockk.proxy\"\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/$version$/mockk-agent-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/mockk/mockk\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/mockk/mockk/tree/$version$/modules/mockk-agent/src/jvmTest\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/$version$/mockk-agent-jvm-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"mockk-agent-jvm is MockK's JVM inline mocking agent for Kotlin tests, using Byte Buddy and Objenesis to create class, constructor, and static proxies. It supplies the runtime instrumentation behind MockK's JVM mocking features, including inline transformation and dispatcher/advice classes used when tests need to mock otherwise hard-to-substitute code.\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/index.json:18:      \"io.mockk.proxy.jvm\"\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/mockk/mockk-core-jvm/$version$/mockk-core-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/mockk/mockk\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/mockk/mockk/tree/$version$/modules/mockk-core/src/j