vm is MockK's JVM inline mocking agent for Kotlin tests, using Byte Buddy and Objenesis to create class, constructor, and static proxies. It supplies the runtime instrumentation behind MockK's JVM mocking features, including inline transformation and dispatcher/advice classes used when tests need to mock otherwise hard-to-substitute code.\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-agent-jvm/index.json:18:      \"io.mockk.proxy.jvm\"\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/mockk/mockk-core-jvm/$version$/mockk-core-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/mockk/mockk\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/mockk/mockk/tree/$version$/modules/mockk-core/src/jvmTest\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/mockk/mockk-core-jvm/$version$/mockk-core-jvm-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"MockK is a Kotlin-first mocking library for creating test doubles, stubbing behavior, and verifying interactions in JVM tests. The mockk-core-jvm artifact provides shared JVM core functionality used by MockK modules, including value-class support and configuration/property loading.\",\n./metadata/io.mockk/mockk-core-jvm/index.json:18:      \"io.mockk.core\"\n./stats/io.mockk/mockk-dsl-jvm/1.14.9/execution-metrics.json:4:    \"library\": \"io.mockk:mockk-dsl-jvm:1.14.9\",\n./stats/io.mockk/mockk-dsl-jvm/1.14.9/execution-metrics.json:59:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/io.mockk/mockk-dsl-jvm/1.14.9/src/test/kotlin/io_mockk/mockk_dsl_jvm/InternalPlatformDslTest.kt\",\n./stats/io.mockk/mockk-dsl-jvm/1.14.9/execution-metrics.json:60:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/io.mockk/mockk-dsl-jvm/1.14.9/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/io.mockk/mockk-cor